// =============================================================================
// core/database/sqlite/native/mod.vr
// =============================================================================
// Layer: 3 (Database — native SQLite implementation)
// Dependencies: core, collections, encoding, security, async, sync, mem, runtime
// Spec: internal/specs/sqlite-native.md
// Codename: loom
// =============================================================================
//
// Pure-Verum reimplementation of SQLite 3.x, layer-structured per
// sqlite-native.md §4:
//
//   L7  API           — Database, Statement, Transaction, Row (public surface)
//   L6  Session       — Connection<Mode>, schema cache, function registry
//   L5  SQL compiler  — lexer, parser, resolver, planner, codegen
//   L4  VDBE          — register-SSA bytecode virtual machine
//   L3  B-tree        — cursors, pages, balance, integrity
//   L2  Record        — varint/serial types/affinity/collation (uses stdlib)
//   L1  Pager         — actor-based, WAL + rollback journal, checkpointer
//   L0  VFS           — VfsProtocol abstraction, MemDbVfs, PosixVfs, Win32Vfs
//
// Orthogonal axes:
//
//   S   Supervision   — supervisor-tree over pager + checkpointer
//   O   Observability — core/tracing spans around every layer
//   V   Verification  — @verify contracts, SMT-discharged B-tree/WAL invariants
//   T   Testing       — DST, differential vs C-SQLite, fuzz (vcs/fuzz/sqlite/)
//
// # Stdlib reuse
//
// loom does NOT duplicate stdlib primitives. Specifically:
//
//   * `core.encoding.varint`         — SQLite varint encoding (Gap 4)
//   * `core.security.hash.crc32`     — WAL frame checksum (Gap 5)
//   * `core.collections.{btree,map}` — in-memory ordered maps for temp tables
//   * `core.mem.arena`               — CBGR arena for page cache
//   * `core.async.{nursery,channel}` — background tasks + actor mailboxes
//   * `core.runtime.supervisor`      — pager + checkpointer supervision
//   * `core.tracing`, `core.metrics` — observability
//   * `core.sys.*`                   — platform I/O, locking, durability
//
// # Status — v0.1 (2026-04-21)
//
// Scaffolded: L0 VfsProtocol, MemDbVfs; L2 Record header parse; L1 Pager
// skeleton. See README.md in this directory for detailed status table.
//
// =============================================================================

module core.database.sqlite.native;

// Layer 0: Virtual File System
public module l0_vfs;

// Layer 1: Pager (actor-based, CBGR page cache, WAL + rollback journal)
public module l1_pager;

// Layer 2: record / type affinity / collation
public module l2_record;

// Layer 3: B-tree (page layout, cursor, balance)
public module l3_btree;

// Layer 4: VDBE (opcodes, register file, interpreter)
public module l4_vdbe;

// Layer 5: SQL (lexer, AST, parser, planner, codegen)
public module l5_sql;

// Layer 6: Session (Connection, SchemaCache, PreparedStatement)
public module l6_session;

// Layer 7: public API (Database facade, DbError)
public module l7_api;

